# Data Flow

The application uses a combination of React Context, custom hooks, and service modules for data management.

## State Management

### Context Providers
- [src/contexts/AuthContext.tsx](mdc:src/contexts/AuthContext.tsx) - Authentication state and user management
- [src/contexts/ThemeContext.tsx](mdc:src/contexts/ThemeContext.tsx) - Theme settings and preferences

### API Services
- [src/services/authService.ts](mdc:src/services/authService.ts) - Authentication API calls
- [src/services/courseService.ts](mdc:src/services/courseService.ts) - Course data management
- [src/services/canvasApi.ts](mdc:src/services/canvasApi.ts) - Canvas API interactions
- [src/services/userDataService.ts](mdc:src/services/userDataService.ts) - User profile and preferences
- [src/services/openaiService.ts](mdc:src/services/openaiService.ts) - OpenAI integration
- [src/services/milestoneService.ts](mdc:src/services/milestoneService.ts) - Learning milestone tracking

## Data Flow Pattern

1. UI Components request data via hooks or context
2. Hooks/Context call appropriate service modules
3. Service modules interact with external APIs (Supabase, etc.)
4. Data flows back up through services to components

## Query Management
The application uses Tanstack Query for API data fetching, caching, and state management.